Architecture plan for Issue #49: Add Tauri app icon set to fix Windows tauri-build resource generation

Scope:
- Packaging/resource-only change for the existing Tauri desktop app.
- Fix Windows tauri-build failure caused by missing src-tauri/icons/icon.ico.
- Expected implementation should only touch src-tauri/tauri.conf.json and add icon assets under src-tauri/icons/.
- Treat "package.metadata does not exist" as non-fatal build noise; do not expand scope to unrelated Cargo/package metadata changes.

Current architecture relevant to this issue:
- Frontend is React + TypeScript + Vite under src/, built to dist/ by npm run build.
- Desktop shell/backend is Tauri 2 + Rust under src-tauri/.
- Tauri configuration lives in src-tauri/tauri.conf.json.
- Native bundle metadata is configured in tauri.conf.json under bundle.*.
- The current bundle.icon array is empty, so tauri-build has no app icon resources to use when generating platform bundles.

Module/file organization:
- Add standard Tauri icon files in src-tauri/icons/:
  - icon.ico: required by Windows resource generation.
  - icon.icns: macOS bundle icon.
  - 32x32.png, 128x128.png, 128x128@2x.png: common cross-platform PNG icons.
- Update src-tauri/tauri.conf.json bundle.icon to reference those paths relative to src-tauri, for example:
  - icons/32x32.png
  - icons/128x128.png
  - icons/128x128@2x.png
  - icons/icon.icns
  - icons/icon.ico

Key design decisions:
- Use the product brand/name from the repository/issue: wonderfulr-d7e0-texdesk.
- Prefer generating the whole icon set from one simple source image to keep assets visually consistent.
- Keep icon assets static and committed; no runtime code path should depend on generation tooling.
- Avoid changing React UI, Rust commands, IPC types, persistence, compile logic, or README unless a build tool requires it.

Dependencies between issues:
- Only Issue #49 is in this planning set, so there are no parallel inter-issue dependencies to coordinate.
- Issue #49 depends conceptually on the existing Tauri packaging setup; implementation should preserve the current productName, identifier, bundle targets, and existing build scripts.

Validation plan for implementation session:
- Confirm src-tauri/tauri.conf.json references all committed icon files.
- Run npm run build to verify frontend/typecheck remains healthy.
- Run npm run tauri:build when platform dependencies are available; at minimum verify the build proceeds past icon/resource lookup on the current platform.
- If full bundling is blocked by missing OS packages/toolchain in the environment, document that and verify icon file existence plus config paths.
